1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,491
But like all progressive companies, we need new products, new markets, new and more efficient ways of doing things.
2
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:10,210
We depend on people with initiative.
3
00:00:10,401 --> 00:00:13,171
They're the ball carriers on our team.
4
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:16,931
Initiative is a special kind of action.
5
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:21,011
It's doing something worthwhile without being told to do it.
6
00:00:21,361 --> 00:00:29,250
The person with initiative has a standing invitation to join the high-income brackets in every business and profession.
7
00:00:29,921 --> 00:00:38,850
The Director of Marketing Research in a medium-sized drug manufacturing firm told me how he got to be a Director of Marketing Research.
8
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:41,891
It's a good lesson in the power of initiative.
9
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:45,730
Five years ago, I got an idea, he told me.
10
00:00:45,921 --> 00:00:50,770
I was working then as a sort of missionary salesman, calling on wholesalers.
11
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:57,330
I discovered that one thing we lacked was facts about the consumers we wanted to buy our drug line.
12
00:00:57,600 --> 00:01:01,330
I talked about the need for market research to everyone here.
13
00:01:01,680 --> 00:01:06,691
At first, I got only deaf ears because management couldn't see the need for it.
14
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:11,810
I was pretty much obsessed with the idea of marketing research in our company,
15
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,531
so I sort of took the bull by the horns.
16
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:20,531
I asked and got permission to prepare a monthly report on facts of drug marketing.
17
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:24,210
I collected information from every source I could find.
18
00:01:24,401 --> 00:01:32,451
I kept on with this, and pretty soon management and the other salesmen found themselves really interested in what I was doing.
19
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:42,611
Just one year after I started crusading for research, I was relieved of my regular duties and asked to concentrate on developing my ideas.
20
00:01:43,361 --> 00:01:47,171
The rest, he continued, was just natural development.
21
00:01:47,361 --> 00:01:54,611
Now I've got two assistants, a secretary, and about three times the yearly income I had five years ago.
22
00:01:56,080 --> 00:02:01,091
Here are two special exercises for developing the initiative habit.
23
00:02:01,091 --> 00:02:02,691
1.
24
00:02:02,881 --> 00:02:04,370
Be a Crusader.
25
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:09,330
When you see something that you believe ought to be done, pick up the ball and run.
26
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:17,651
A new subdivision not far from where I live was about two-thirds built when expansion came almost to a standstill.
27
00:02:17,921 --> 00:02:21,730
A few families with a don't-care attitude had moved in.
28
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:27,546
This prompted several of the finest families in the area to sell their homes at a loss and move on.
